## Goal

Wire RoutingConfig and ResourceTopology into the actual startup sequence in listener.rs.
This is the integration bead that connects all the v1 routing work to the running server.

## CONTEXT: The actual startup sequence lives here

File: src/protocol/rest/listener.rs
Function: build_shared_state(config: &RestConfig) -> RefusalResult<Arc<RestSharedState>>

Current call sequence (lines ~252-293):
```rust
fn build_shared_state(config: &RestConfig) -> RefusalResult<Arc<RestSharedState>> {
    let catalog = load_rest_catalog(&config.spec_path)?;  // OpenApiDoc consumed here
    // ...
    let registry = build_route_registry(&catalog);          // no config, no topology
    // ...
}
```

The v1 call sequence must be:
```rust
fn build_shared_state(config: &RestConfig) -> RefusalResult<Arc<RestSharedState>> {
    // 1. Load spec (OpenApiDoc — do NOT consume yet)
    let (catalog, x_ext) = load_rest_catalog_with_extensions(&config.spec_path)?;
    //    ^ parse x-twinning BEFORE or DURING catalog build (see bd-v2s6 for approach)

    // 2. Resolve routing config from CLI + x-twinning extension
    let routing_config = resolve_routing_config(
        config.routing_policy,    // from RestConfig (added in bd-v1r.2)
        config.base_prefix.clone(),
        x_ext.as_ref(),
    );

    // 3. Build spec topology (global, all evidence sources)
    let topology = build_spec_topology(&catalog, &routing_config);

    // 4. Build route registry (topology lookup + waterfall fallback)
    let registry = build_route_registry(&catalog, &topology, &routing_config);

    // 5. Print startup routing report (confidence + conflict columns)
    let report = RoutingReport::from_registry(&registry);
    report.log_at_startup();

    // 6. Continue as before...
}
```

